Utterance: Hi! Welcome back! How have you been since our last session?
Hey! I’ve been doing pretty well. I performed at the open mic night!
That’s amazing! How did it go?
It was awesome! I was nervous at first, but once I got on stage, it felt great.
That’s wonderful to hear! What was the highlight of the performance for you?
Just the energy from the crowd. They were really into it, and it felt like we were all connected.
That connection is powerful. How did it feel to share your music with others?
It felt liberating. I love expressing myself that way.
That’s fantastic! Have you thought about what you want to do next in your music journey?
I want to keep performing and maybe start recording some tracks.
That sounds like a solid plan! Have you made any progress on recording?
I’ve set aside some time this week to start working on a demo.
That’s great! Setting aside time is a crucial step. What do you hope to achieve with this demo?
I want to capture my sound and share my story. It’s important to me.
Your story is a valuable part of your music. How do you feel about the process of recording?
I’m excited but also a bit nervous. I want it to be perfect.
Perfection can be a tough standard to hold yourself to. Remember that it’s okay to make mistakes and learn as you go.
Yeah, I need to remind myself of that.
It’s all part of the creative process. Have you thought about what you’ll do if you face challenges while recording?
I think I’ll just take breaks and not rush things.
That’s a healthy approach. Taking breaks can help you stay focused and avoid burnout.
For sure. I want to enjoy the process.
Enjoying the process is key. Is there anything else on your mind today?
I’ve been feeling a bit anxious about my friendships lately.
What’s been causing that anxiety?
I feel like I’m growing and changing, but some friends want to stay in the same routine.
It’s common for friendships to evolve as we grow. Have you talked to them about how you’re feeling?
Not yet. I’m worried about how they’ll react.
It’s understandable to feel that way. Open communication can help strengthen your friendships.
I guess I just need to be honest about where I’m at.
Honesty can lead to deeper connections. Would you like to practice how you might approach that conversation?
Yeah, that’d be helpful.
Great! You might start by expressing your feelings and how important their friendship is to you.
Okay, like, “Hey, I value our friendship, but I feel like I’m changing and want to talk about it?”
Exactly! That opens the door for a constructive conversation. How does that feel to say?
It feels good. I think I can do that.
I believe you can! It’s all about being true to yourself.
Thanks! I’ll try to have that conversation soon.
I’m looking forward to hearing how it goes. Remember, it’s okay to prioritize your own growth.
For sure. I appreciate your support.
Of course! I’m here for you. Let’s keep working on your goals together.
Sounds good! Bye!
Bye! Take care!
